<section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-4 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
      Why attribution is broken
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
      The tools that should help you are working against you.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">GA4 killed your model choice</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">First-touch, linear, time-decay — all gone. Now you get last-click or a black-box "data-driven" model you can't inspect.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Platforms grade their own homework</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">Facebook says Facebook works. Google says Google works. Shocking. Their inflated ROAS numbers don't match reality.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Ad blockers eat 30% of your data</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">Client-side tracking misses nearly a third of visitors. You're making budget decisions on incomplete data.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Enterprise pricing for basic features</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">Enterprise tools want annual contracts and sales calls. Attribution shouldn't require a finance committee.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-12 scroll-animate" data-controller="scroll-reveal">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">See how mbuzz solves these problems</p>
      <%= link_to demo_path, class: "inline-flex items-center px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 bg-white border border-blue-600 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-50 transition-all" do %>
        Try the Demo
        <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
